  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Stabilisation Advisor - Stabilisation Unit, UK</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is an agreement for the temporary placement of a Danida Stabilisation Adviser to be deployed to the Stabilisation Unit in London, United Kingdom. The initial period of deployment is two years from spring 2015 under the Danida Long Term Stabilisation Adviser Regulations.

The Stabilisation Advisers&#xBF; responsibilities are to include but not be limited to: Participating in British activities of stabilisation in fragile and conflict affected areas; Providing written analysis, reports and briefings within relevant stabilisation-related areas; Following important developments related to strategy, planning and implementation of stabilisation policies; Providing a line of communication between Denmark and the United Kingdom in the stabilisation agenda and enhance cooperation and complementarity between the two.</narrative>
  </description>
